Removal update  Unknown ([edit](https://oldschool.runescape.wiki/w/Grid_Master?action=edit))      **Grid Master** is a [community event](/w/Community_Event) launched on [15 October](/w/15_October) [2025](/w/2025), running for four weeks. Grid Master is a temporary game mode where players start with fresh accounts to complete tasks presented in a 7x7 bingo grid. Completing any individual task will provide a reward, while completing full rows or columns of the grid will give the player special, more powerful rewards.

## Overview
 Grid Master is a bingo-based community event. Players compete to complete tasks presented to them in a 7x7 grid. Completing tasks will grant rewards for use on the Grid Master community event worlds and accumulate Grid Points for use in purchasing rewards on the main game worlds. Grid Master is accessible both by members and free-to-play players, with the latter being able to complete the seven tasks in column 4, as well as three additional tasks in row 4 for a total of 10 tasks worth 1,000 Grid Points.[[1]](#cite_note-1) 
The bingo grid system is intended to be polled for implementation within the main game worlds as well. Players would be able to design their own task lists and share with others.[[2]](#cite_note-2) 
 
## Rules
 

- All players start as a fresh [Ironman](/w/Ironman).
 
- All players start with the following multipliers: - a 5x (+400%) [experience](/w/Experience) multiplier - a 5x [slayer points](/w/Slayer_reward_point) multiplier - a 5x [Farming growth rate](/w/Farming#Growth_timing) multiplier - an 8x [drop rates](/w/Drop_rates) multiplier for eligible drops - an 4x [minigame](/w/Minigame) points multiplier for eligible minigames - *Note: Experience multipliers can be further enhanced with unlocks.*
 
- All players start with a [dramen staff](/w/Dramen_staff) and the necessary quests unlocked to travel with [fairy rings](/w/Fairy_rings)
 
- Some [quests](/w/Quests) that provide area access are unlocked at the start, such as [The Corsair Curse](/w/The_Corsair_Curse), however others are not, such as [Song of the Elves](/w/Song_of_the_Elves).
 
- [Shops](/w/Shops) have unlimited stock.
 
- No experience rewards can be claimed from [Nightmare Zone](/w/Nightmare_Zone), [Pest Control](/w/Pest_Control), or [Soul Wars](/w/Soul_Wars).

 
## Tasks and unlocks
 As players complete tile tasks, as well as fill out rows or columns of tiles on the grid, they will be granted special rewards to enhance their journey. These unlocks include powerful items, quest auto-completions, and relics. Some of these items and relics will be from prior [Leagues](/w/Leagues).
